<br>
Fact: verant HAS used &quot;softcaps&quot; in the past on other skills/attributes, and clips a number of other calculations (i.e. fall damage, etc).  Very well established they used em on wis/int for mana calculation, indications there might be some on resists, etc.  Very possible that a similar type of coding exists on other calculations, such as melee damage.<br>
<br>
My point in the last post is that you can't tell between the two equally &quot;simple&quot; explainations until you a). exceed the threshold value or b). show experimentally or via industrial espionage none exists.<br>
<br>
