<br>
All the data shown and testing done to date that says there's a &quot;cap&quot; simply isn't conclusive- all that ANY of the posted tests show is that, for the AC range tested and the player/buffs/debuffs/mobs in question, no dropoff in damage was seen.  Right?  Am I missing any relevant data here?<br>
<br>
That's ENTIRELY equivalent and consistent to TWO different situations, NEITHER OF WHICH CAN BE PROVEN CONCLUSIVELY.<br>
<br>
1). There IS a softcap w/ velious and/or luclin, and it's in the 1200-1400-ish range.<br>
<br>
2). There ISN'T a softcap, but the &quot;uber&quot; mobs in question are high enough level (some 70+), have high enough ATK (stats or combat table), etc. that they &quot;overpower&quot; ACs up to the tested 1500ish range.  Think level 50 player in oldworld gear vs. Seb protector; no matter what oldworld armor he's wearing, it isn't going to reduce the damage he takes.<br>
<br>
Number 1 would be &quot;consistent&quot; with the way verant implemented old world/kunark soft caps.  Number 2 would be consistent with how the combat engine works on ACs &lt;&lt; a softcap.  You can't tell the difference, at least from the testing done to date.<br>
<br>
For example, even tests with large AC ranges (from 1200-1500) show that there is no massive dropoff in damage done, rather that it's fairly constant over the range.  That in itself suggests that there isn't a &quot;soft&quot; cap at all, otherwise the damage (mode, dps, whatever) should gradually diminish with AC, correct?  From what's been posted, it doesnt... which actually suggests the tester is still in the &quot;gets hit hard a lot&quot; AC range, not above a softcap or near a knee in the dmg vs. AC curve.<br>
<br>
The testing I can do with the gear I have has already been shown (with varying degrees of clarity) to be flat- Remf can only hit the low-mid 1400's fully geared up, not even close to the full NTOV gear folks.  I have tanked most of the mobs in velious (basically all but statue/AoW/Tunare), and a couple of the new luclin ubers, and logged a few of them.  Nothing I saw in them was conclusive at all, as expected.   AFIK a softcap isn't provable OR disprovable, unless someone has the number for the psychic friends network and/or a bribeable verant coder handy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
